TY  - JOUR
TI  - Efficiency of Large Double Auctions
AU  - Cripps, Martin W.
AU  - Swinkels, Jeroen M.
AB  - [We consider large double auctions with private values. Values need be neither symmetric nor independent. Multiple units may be owned or desired. Participation may be stochastic. We introduce a very mild notion of "a little independence." We prove that all nontrivial equilibria of auctions that satisfy this notion are asymptotically efficient. For any α > 0, inefficiency disappears at rate $1/n^{2-\alpha}$.]
